<HEADLINE> King Hassan II of Morocco Begins Visit to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- King Hassan II of Morocco began
Monday afternoon a state visit to France, during which he will be
the guest of President Jacques Chirac to attend the July 14
Bastille Day military parade on the Champs-Elysee Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
King Hassan II will focus his talks with Chirac and Prime
Minister Lionel Jospin on bilateral economic cooperation and
Morocco's economic reforms aimed at tackling problems of
unemployment, low economic growth rate and foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
The Socialist government of Jospin has promised to help Morocco
carry out social and economic reforms through establishing joint
ventures and making other forms of investment.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Morocco and Algeria are likely to be a big
topic between the leaders of France and Morocco, as France has
strategic security interests in the Maghreb region.
</P>
<P>
Morocco and Algeria have experienced tense relations since
1994, when an armed attack took place on a hotel in Marrakech, in
which Morocco suspected involvement of Algerian security service.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the visit by the Moroccan monarchy, some human
rights groups have called on the French government to pressure
Morocco to allow an Moroccan opposition leader living in exile in
France to return home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
