<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Leading Insurer Goes International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Old Mutual, South Africa's
leading insurer, was Monday successfully listed in five stock
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The company was listed in London, Zimbabwe, Namibia and Malawi
as well as in Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
The issue price of 11.25 rand was lower than expected, but it
made rapid initial gain. In Johannesburg, it closed at 13.10 rand
(2.18 U.S. dollars) on Monday, according to the SABC television.
</P>
<P>
The listing of Old Mutual, which was demutualized in May this
year, sparked speculation of a six-billion-rand (one billion
dollars) spending spree in South Africa as policy holders swap
their free share for cash.
</P>
<P>
At the initial price of 11.25 rand, the Old Mutual group was
worth 6.1 billion dollars, a valuation which would catapult it
into the FTSE 100 index.
</P>
<P>
Old Mutual follows mining groups Billiton and Anglo American as
the latest South African company to be listed in London. 
</P>
</TEXT>
