The OAU, which chooses to attribute the two prizes, one for a
French - speaking country, another for an English-speaking
country, also consider other criteria for the award, such as the
traditions of receiving massive displaced people and their
participation in the re-establishment of peace, the official said.
</P>
<P>
There are about 6.5 million refugees in Africa, which is
plagued by armed conflicts and instability in many parts of the
continent.
</P>
<P>
