<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Today (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of today'
s diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
China-Australia Ties Hailed
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting here today with Australia's
Foreign Minister Alexander Downer, said that China is willing to
make joint efforts with Australia to establish bilateral ties in
the 21st century with long-term stability and healthy growth.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that both nations have a great influence in the Asia-
Pacific region and have a common interest in guarding regional
peace and stability and promoting regional prosperity and
development.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan also held talks with Downer. Tang
said that the Chinese government firmly opposes any attempt by the
Taiwan authorities to create "two Chinas" or "one China, one
Taiwan" in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral ties have been on the track of all-round
development in recent years and added that China and Australia
have had good dialog and cooperation in some major international
and regional issues, while the mechanism for consultation and
dialog between the two countries has been strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Downer told Chinese Foreign Trade Minister Shi Guangsheng that
Australia backs China's entry into the WTO as soon as possible and
hopes that bilateral talks on China's WTO entry can be concluded
very soon.
</P>
