<HEADLINE> Pak Urges Int'l Community to Help Settle Kashmir Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Monday said now the
ball is in the court of international community which should press
New Delhi for an "expeditious political settlement" of the Kashmir
dispute.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Office spokesman Tariq Altaf told a news
briefing that now that the Mujahideen (freedom fighters) have
decided to "disengage" in Kargil, the international community has
an opportunity to press for an expeditious political settlement of
the dispute for which dialogue should be resumed "as quickly as
possible".
</P>
<P>
"The ball is in the court of international community - the
responsibility to address the Kashmir dispute is universal so that
a Kargil-like situation does not reappear," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, he said, has been calling for dialogue to address the
Kashmir issue and the international community "should use its
influence and bring New Delhi to negotiating table for settlement
of the dispute".
</P>
<P>
The spokesman referred to U.S. President Bill Clinton's
commitment and "personal interest" in the intensification of the
efforts and the process of dialogue for resolution of the issue.
</P>
<P>
He said this Kargil episode has made the larger issue of
Kashmir dispute very clearly visible on the international horizon.
</P>
<P>
"The Mujahideen's cause has been very widely publicized and it
has been understood that this dispute should be resolved if we
wish to see peace and security in the region," he asserted.
</P>
</TEXT>
