<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France, Iraq Hold Talks on Proposal to U.N. Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- French and Iraqi officials have been
holding talks in Baghdad, New York and Paris on a French proposal
for lifting economic sanctions on Baghdad, which Paris plans to
present to the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted the chief of the French section of
interests in Baghdad, Andre Janier, as saying that the talks with
Iraqi officials have been constructive and positive.
</P>
<P>
"We talk with the Iraqi authorities each day on the subject of
French ideas, either in Baghdad, or with the Iraqi diplomats in
Paris, or in New York through contacts of French and Iraqi
diplomats," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that France wishes to take into account all the
positive elements in the British proposal and the Russian proposal
on Iraq, so that all the members of the U.N. Security Council can
accept it.
</P>
<P>
The French diplomat estimated that the U.N. Security Council
has "attained an impasse" over Iraq.
</P>
<P>
It is only through dialogue between different member countries
of the Council can a solution be found, he said.
</P>
<P>
The British proposal includes a 120-day renewable suspension of
the embargo on Iraqi exports, if the Iraqi government meets its
commitment on disarmament.
</P>
<P>
The French proposal includes a 100-day renewable suspension of
embargo on both exports and imports by Iraq, and the establishment
of a new regime of supervision of Iraqi armament to replace the
U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM). 
</P>
</TEXT>
