<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Among Best in Human Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
is among countries that perform best in human development,
according to a United Nations report released on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report assessed the quality of life in 174 countries based
on real income, life expectancy and educational standards, and it
divided the countries into three lists based on the rich and poor
quality of life, the official WAM news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The UAE, ranked 43, was put in the first list which realized a
high record in human development, the agency said, adding that
other Gulf countries in the first list included Kuwait, Bahrain
and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and Oman came in the second list which comprised
95 countries including Arab countries such as Libya, Lebanon,
Jordan, Syria, Egypt and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Sudan and Yemen came in the third list which included 35
countries of low development.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. report said that the increasing trend toward
globalization did not have to be a bad thing provided governments
took into account more than just trade issues when they were
considering international policy.
</P>
<P>
The aim is to put human concerns at the center of the
globalization debate, to focus on the global interdependence of
people and not just of financial flows, WAM quoted the report
as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
