<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills 15 People in Western Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people are reportedly
dead and dozens injured on Monday in a landslide caused by
torrential rain and floods at a dam in the Western Romania Retezat
Mountains.
</P>
<P>
On Monday morning, the upper waters of the Rau Mare river in
the western county of Hunedoara flooded the construction side of
the dam and weakened it by removing several rocks, then a wall of
mud and water hit the houses sheltering some 100 families employed
at the construction of the dam. The mud covered houses up to the
first floor, an eyewitness was reported as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to Nicolae Stanca, prefect of Hunedoara, 22 people
had been injured and 13 were reported missing. The rescue teams
reached the disaster area by helicopters and flew the injured
persons to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The rescue teams tried to evacuate families out of the disaster
area, but some workers refused to leave saying they wanted to find
the missing ones.
</P>
<P>
Two school camps were also in the disaster area, but out of
danger. All measures for their being transferred to other similar
camps in the county were taken, authorities in charge reported.
</P>
<P>
In the latest 24 hours, storms and torrential rains flooded
thousands of houses and caused huge damages in western and central
Romania, when the southern and eastern Romania were still facing
the long-lasting heat wave which has killed at least 20 people.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists are not announcing any weather improvement.
Moreover, they are saying that temperatures may increase by two or
three degrees and reach over 40 grades Celsius. Heavy rains and
storms may also occur any time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
