<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Mixed At Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- London stock market bore the brunt
of the early course reversal on Wall Street, as banking stocks led
it to a negative close Monday.
</P>
<P>
The downturn on Wall Street in early trade hit sentiment across
the board, with the Dow Jones industrial average some 20 points
lower as London closed.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 ended 17.1 points lower at 6545.5, a fall of 0.26
percent, after a choppy session that saw the leading index
fluctuate in and out of the red in a tight trading range.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks did the damage in London, with heavyweight
Lloyds TSB leading the way as it closed down 2.38 percent. NatWest
Bank suffered even more to end the session 3.77 percent down,
while Barclays shed 2.14 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany's leading shares closed up slightly on the day as
markets moved toward fresh highs for the year.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Dax index closed up despite attention this week
being on the troubled euro and key economic data due in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The Dax finished 0.23 percent up at 5652.02 points. Traders
said the mood was still good, buoyed by rises in chemical stocks
and despite profit-taking falls by some banks.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 posted a gain of 14.45 points to end at
4662.28, a gain of 0.31 percent, some 35 points short of its
record close. 
</P>
</TEXT>
