<HEADLINE> 50th Anniversary Of China Federation of Literary and Art Circles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- On the occasion of the 50th
anniversary of the China Federation of Literary and Art Circles (
CFLAC), a celebration was held in the Great Hall of the People for
several generations of artists to talk about the past and look
forward to the future.
</P>
<P>
CFLAC has achieved a lot since it was set up in July of 1949,
the year when the new China was founded, and more masterpieces
have emerged especially after the reforms and opening up,
according to Gao Zhanxiang, its vice president.
</P>
<P>
CFLAC has been dedicated, together with overseas Chinese
artists, to promoting Chinese culture and has helped in promoting
international cultural exchanges and its international reputation
is increasing, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese nation needs more masterpieces and CFLAC will help
build a healthy environment to boost Chinese culture, he said.
</P>
<P>
CFLAC is a non-governmental organization with 49 branches with
more than two million registered members and more than 40
publications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
