<HEADLINE> China's Tourism Businesses Looking At Markets Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China's tourism businesses have
decided to get more foreign tourists through a series of promotion
campaigns that target major overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
He Guangwei, the director of China's National Tourism
Administration, told a national tourism marketing symposium here
today that the major tasks of the next 3 to 5 years should be
studying market demands and providing tourist products.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas tourists in the January-May period was
up 14 percent compared with the same period of last year. They
came from Asia, Europe, North America, and Oceanic countries.
</P>
<P>
Businesses are being asked to focus on new markets in South
Africa, India, the Middle-East, and neighboring countries.
</P>
