<HEADLINE> More Multinationals Investing In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Sources from Shanghai's Pudong
New Area say that the area got 924 million U.S.dollars worth of
investment in the January-June period of this year, 400 million
dollars of that from multinationals.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Bell Telephone Equipment Manufacturing Co.Ltd added
110 million U.S. dollars worth of investment in the first half of
the year. Intel added investment for the second time in six months,
bringing its total 95 million U.S. dollars to 198 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
An official at Hitachi said that it has added investment three
times because of the favorable investment environment in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Over 80 percent of the multinationals in Pudong are showing a
profit.
</P>
<P>
Total investment by U.S. enterprises surpassed that of Hong
Kong companies this year, putting the U.S. in first place.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
