<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Granted Spanish Cup Bye </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Real Madrid has been granted a bye
through to the last 16 of the Spanish Cup next season by the
Spanish Football League (LPF) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The LPF made the decision after considering the fixture
congestion caused by their participation in the world club
championship.
</P>
<P>
According to the original arrangement, Real had to compete in
the fourth round in early January, when they will be in Brazil for
the new tournament. 
</P>
