<HEADLINE> Summer Bringing More Tourists To China's World Horticulture Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The World Horticulture Exposition
in the Chinese city of Kunming has reported an increase in the
number of visitors, especially students, this month, when summer
holiday began, according to Yang Yun, the director of the
Organizing Committee's press center.
</P>
<P>
Preparing for the increase of visitors, transportation
departments have increased the number of passenger trains between
Kunming and some major Chinese cities like Nanjing, Fuzhou,
Guangzhou, and Chongqing. Yunnan Airlines has also provided
discounts for students and teachers.
</P>
<P>
In order to attract more student visitors, the organizing
committee has decided to cut the admission price for students,
Yang said.
</P>
<P>
The exposition ends at the end of October and is expected to
have eight to ten million visitors from China and abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
