<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) increased slightly Tuesday, closing at
4,615.20 points as against Monday's close of 4,585.63, gaining a
modest rise of 29.57 points.
</P>
<P>
Within seconds after resumption of trading, the sensex surged
past the all-time peak of 4,643.31 points recorded on September
12, 1994, hitting the historical high of 4,678.28.
</P>
<P>
However, it later reflected the downward price resistance and
dropped drastically.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed late selling to the reported shift of
activity by players to the National Stock Exchange (NSE) which
offered comparatively cheaper quotes by the end of trading.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index improved further by 8.72 points to 1,990.35
from the previous close of 1,981.64.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the dollex were quoted moderately up at 455.32
and 175.35 points compared with previous close of 453.25 and
174.52 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Delhi Sensex rose slightly by 1.17 points,
closing at 1,009.10 as against Monday's 1,007.93 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
