<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Cyprus Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists visiting
Cyprus during the first five months of 1999 shows an increase of
9.5 percent compared to the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released Tuesday by Cyprus' Department
of Statistics and Research, for the period January-May 1999,
arrivals of tourists reached 711,670 compared to 649,786 in the
corresponding period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The overwhelming majority of the tourists were from European
Union countries with Britain ranking first with 50 percent of
the arrivals.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show that in May 1999, the number of
excursionists, cruise-ship visitors and transit at ports or
airports reached 8,861.
</P>
<P>
Tourism, the main foreign currency earner for Cyprus,
contributes 20 percent of the country's gross national product
(GNP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
