<HEADLINE> Australian News Makes Chinese Book Donation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian News Corporation
donated a number of copies of the Macquarie English-Chinese
Dictionary to the National Library of China today.
</P>
<P>
The dictionary is a translation of the Macquarie Dictionary
that was done by the Australian Studies Center at Suzhou
University, which was published in May by the Suzhou University
Press.
</P>
<P>
Australian News's representative in Beijing, Laurie Smith, said
at a donation ceremony that the dictionary will provide a useful
reference for students, teachers and researchers and help to
increase understanding and cooperation between the people of
Australia and China.
</P>
<P>
The Macquarie Dictionary provides a unique Australian outlook
on words and usage in the English language. Autralian News is one
of the world's largest media companies, with total assets worth 36
billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
