<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks closed
marginally lower Tuesday as the 100-share price index fell 4.58
points, or 0.40 percent, to 1,135.07.
</P>
<P>
The volume Tuesday stood at 203.361 million shares against
Monday's 155.329 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Profit-taking by foreign investors brought the market down
despite the positive reaction by the domestic dealers to Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif's Monday speech on the Kashmir issue,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 133 active issues, losers beat gainers 57 to 45 while 31
remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
