<HEADLINE> Chirac Urges N.Ireland Parties to Accept Peace Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac said
on Tuesday that France offers its entire support to the peace
efforts by Britain and Ireland in Northern Ireland and called on
all the parties in the British province to accept the peace plan.
</P>
<P>
The new plan proposed on July 2 by British Prime Minister Tony
Blair and Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern "helps move forward
reconciliation, renouncement of force and disarmament at the same
time," said Chirac in a published statement.
</P>
<P>
"The French people strongly hope that all the parties could
accept it. It is important for the United Kingdom and Ireland of
course, but also for the whole Europe," he said.
</P>
<P>
The British-Irish peace plan includes the creation by July 15
of a new local government in Northern Ireland to be shared by
Catholic and Protestant communities, and disarmament of
paramilitary forces by both sides in May 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
