<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members from Hong Kong on Closer Ties With Mainland's Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A 58-member delegation from the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) say that there
should be closer cooperation with Yunnan Province in developing
its rich resources.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong members of the Chinese People's Political and
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee met with Yunnan
's Governor Li Jiating and Vice-governor Huang Bingsheng recently
after a week-long visit that began on July 5 to the provincial
capital, Kunming, and to the towns of Dali and Lijiang.
</P>
<P>
They said that there is a great potential in developing herbal
medicines. Yunnan has listed pharmaceuticals as a pillar industry
for the 21st century and Hong Kong wants to become a global herbal
medicine center.
</P>
<P>
They also pointed to Yunnan's tourism resources, its ethnic
groups, folk customs, beautiful scenic spots, and historical
relics and talked about the coordinated development of tourism.
</P>
<P>
Li Donghai, the head of the delegation who is a member of 9th
CPPCC National Committee's Standing Committee, said that a 1
million yuan education fund is being established in Hong Kong to
support the development of higher learning in Yunnan. By July 11,
it had received 279,000 yuan in donations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
