<HEADLINE> China to Issue More T-Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China will issue treasury bonds
with a value of 50 billion yuan to private investors on July 16.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second issue of treasury bonds to individuals
this year, the first batch having been issued in March.
</P>
<P>
The registered bonds include 35 billion yuan worth of three-
year bonds and 15 billion yuan worth of five-year bonds.
</P>
<P>
The three-year bonds have an annual interest rate of 3.02
percent, and the five-year bonds have an annual interest rate of 3.
25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance announced the decision to issue the
bonds after issuing 20 billion yuan worth of treasury bonds to
corporate investors today.
</P>
<P>
Since the interest rates on savings deposits have been
significantly reduced and are expected to be cut even further,
individual investors are enthusiastic about buying treasury bonds
which have higher interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The registered bonds will be sold at banks and post offices
across the country from July 16 to August 31. However, previous
issues have shown that the bonds will be sold out far sooner than
the later date, and in some big cities such as Beijing they may be
sold out in less than one week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
