Armado Cruz Neto has said that the Angolan government troops are
preparing for a decisive offensive against the UNITA rebels soon.
</P>
<P>
The Journal of Angola newspaper Tuesday quoted the official as
saying that the rebel forces of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) are launching sneak attacks on the
government army.
</P>
<P>
The rebels are mainly engaged in planting land mines along the
roads, ambushing the government convoy fleets, bombing the
strategic towns and attacking villages, said Neto.
</P>
<P>
Despite the constant attacks by the rebels, the government
troops are controlling the general situation of the country, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister disclosed that the government troops have
advanced at several front lines, citing the successful operation
in the town of Sanza Pombo in northern Uige Province and the
central city of Huambo.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government said repeatedly that it would launch a
large- scale offensive during the dry season so as to wipe out the
military forces of the UNITA led by Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the UNITA forces have reportedly been launching
sneak attacks on innocent people to create a wave of refugees and
exert political and social pressure upon the Angolan government in
a bid to delay the destructive hit from the army. 
</P>
