<HEADLINE> Czech Unemployment Rate Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate of the Czech
Republic has hit a new record high of 8.4 percent, the Labor and
Social Affairs Ministry said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 435,000 people were registered unemployed by the end of
June, which means a 2.4 percent increase over the same period of
last year, an official of the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the unemployment rate will exceed 10
percent by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Many enterprises are facing bankruptcy in the ongoing
government-launched readjustment of economic structures. That was
believed to be the main reason of the unemployment rate increase.
</P>
<P>
The Czech government have started a national employment program
to create more job opportunities. 
</P>
