<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Fall 0.58 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed down 80.
91 points, or 0.58 percent, at 13,980.93 Tuesday on fear of more
placements into the market.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover decreased to 8.082 billion HK dollars (1.
036 billion U.S. dollars), as against 8.372 billion HK dollars (1.
073 billion U.S. dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say investors are still in fear that some blue chips
would try to raise cash through placements despite the recent
losses in the market.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, only finance gained 0.11 percent,
while utilities, properties and commerce &AMP; industry, all suffered
losses of 1.12 percent, 0.84 percent and 0.82 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares closed lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 0.52 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index up 2.10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The share prices dropped 4.58 points, or 0.03 percent, to open
at 14,057.26 Tuesday morning. The market became weaker and closed
the morning session at 14,013.28 points. 
