<HEADLINE> India to Auction Government Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Reserve Bank of India will
auction 25 billion rupees (575 million U.S. dollars), or 12.32
percent, of government stock maturing in 2011.
</P>
<P>
The auction will be held on July 25. With this, the bank said,
the government will complete 52 percent of its budgeted borrowing
program of 835.71 billion rupees (19.2 billion U.S. dollars) for
1999-2000.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the auction will suck out liquidity from the
money market and lead to tightness. The paper is currently trading
at 101.30/40 rupees (2.33 U.S. dollars) level.
</P>
<P>
The price is likely to go down in the coming days on account of
tight liquidity conditions as no significant inflows are expected,
they added. 
