<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Customs Smashes Pirated Optical Discs Factory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs officers
smashed an unlicensed optical discs factory Monday following the
seizure of two production lines and more than 3,000 pirated
optical discs, totally worth more than 12 million HK dollars (1.54
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Three men, aged between 16 and 30, were arrested in the raid.
They will be charged with offenses in relation with operating a CD
factory without a valid license and possession of pirated articles
for commercial purpose.
</P>
<P>
"The on-going anti-piracy operations demonstrate the government
's determination in combating piracy activities and preserving the
good image of Hong Kong," said a spokesman for the Customs and
Excise Department.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers had so far this year smashed six unlicensed
optical discs factories and impounded eight production lines,
worth about 34 million HK dollars in total, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Customs officers seized 39 million pirated optical
discs worth 0.96 billion HK dollars and arrested 1,645 people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
