<DOCNO> XIE19990713.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loans to Tuvalu for Self-sufficient Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
approved Tuesday a 4-million-U.S. dollar concessionary loan to
help the outer islands of the Pacific nation of Tuvalu become more
self-sufficient.
</P>
<P>
In a news release issued here, the ADB said the Island
Development Program will help to shift responsibility for managing
development programs in the outer islands from the central
government to local government.
</P>
<P>
"Such a program will foster regional development by providing a
macroeconomic policy framework, delivering much-needed support
services and promoting business development," the ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The loan will come from the ADB's Asian Development Fund and
will have a maturity of 24 years, including a grace period of
eight years.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate will be 1 percent per annum during the grace
period and 1.5 percent per annum thereafter, the ADB said.
</P>
</TEXT>
