<HEADLINE> Upswing in Banks Help Australian Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
finished higher on Tuesday, with firmer banking and finance
stocks providing much of the upswing.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index added 13.7 points to 3063.9,
drifting from an intra-day peak of 3071.1 points.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the upswing has been generally in the banking and
finance sector and that is really due to our bonds being much,
much higher than they were yesterday," said Reynolds &AMP; Co adviser
Peter Struk.
</P>
<P>
Struk also said weakness among resource stocks on Tuesday held
the market back.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index climbed 34.6 points to 5311.0, while
the all resources index shed 7.2 to an even 1300.0.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth Bank surged 40 cents, or 1.67 percent, to
24.35 Australian dollars, National Australia Bank rallied 17.8 to
24.378 Australian dollars, Westpac firmed 12 to 9.75 Australian
dollars and ANZ rose 9.5 to 11.165 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 526.19 million stocks traded for 1.2
billion Australian dollars (792 billion U.S. dollars). Falling
stocks outnumbered rising stocks 640 to 597 and 423 stocks
remained steady. 
</P>
