<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices ended lower on
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as weak buying prevailed in the
wake of last week's selloff in penny stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) closed at 2,178.49
points, 20.29 points lower than Monday.
</P>
<P>
The volume decreased 533.52 million shares worth 635.50 million
Singapore dollars (375.53 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outnumbered gainers by 317 to 42 with 85 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
GoldenAg continued to lead the volume list with a turnover of
44.90 million shares. It was followed by AFP that had 28.30
million units done. Hotung was the next with 21.99 million
counters traded.
</P>
<P>
SPH remained in its position as the biggest gainer running up
100 cents to close at 31.70 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 also kept
its second rank rising 90 cents to finish at 31.70 Singapore
dollars. SIA climbed by 40 cents to end at 14.50 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture headed the descent of the day losing
50 cents to close at 14.40 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 and DBS
each shed 40 cents to finish at 21.10 and 17.90 Singapore dollars
respectively. C&AMP;C retreated 35 cents to end at 9.35 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that trading was dominated by selective buying in
banks and blue chips and second liner or penny stocks were not
expected to do well.
</P>
<P>
They said that trading had been listless after a selloff last
week in penny stocks triggered across the board selling.
</P>
<P>
They noted that sentiment was weak as market players looked for
fresh news. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
