<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The cease-fire agreement on the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), which was recently signed in
Lusaka, Zambia by all the countries involved in the conflict, will
facilitate refugee work in the country.
</P>
<P>
United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNCHR) Sadako
Ogata made the remarks at a news briefing here Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
