official said that President Kabila promised to handle this issue
according to the will of the refugees. They could remain in Congo
(K) if they wanted to, she said.
</P>
<P>
The 11-month armed conflict in Congo (K) generated hundreds of
thousands of refugees who fled to neighboring countries including
Tanzania, Uganda and others.
</P>
<P>
She urged leaders of countries participating in the conflict to
honor and implement the cease-fire agreement in earnest, because
she noted peace and stability is the only hope for resolving the
refugee crisis in the Great Lakes region. 
