<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Speaker Stresses Cooperation with Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese parliament speaker
has stressed his country's keenness on strengthening cooperation
with Egypt in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette newspaper reported on Tuesday that
Chairman of the Vietnamese National Assembly Nong Duc Manh told
Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal El-Ganzouri during a meeting on
Monday that Vietnam gives priority to the agricultural cooperation
with Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Nong, who arrived in Cairo on Sunday, discussed with
El-Ganzouri various ways of bolstering the economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two men also reviewed the developments of the Middle East
peace process, which is hopeful to make progress now that the
moderate Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak has taken office.
</P>
<P>
Nong Duc Manh also held talks on Monday with Egyptian Deputy
Prime Minister and Minister of Agriculture Youssef Wali on
necessary steps to accelerate cooperation between the two
countries, the pro-government newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed the possibility of exchanging expertise
in the agricultural field, including joint efforts to improve the
productivity of sugar cane and rice through genetic engineering
and advanced irrigation machines.
</P>
<P>
Wali told Nong that Egypt is keen to implement the trade
agreements and the education cooperation pact signed recently with
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Both Wali and Nong underlined the importance of consolidating
the parliamentary cooperation between Egypt and Vietnam. 
</P>
