<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Truce Panel Convenes in South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The international monitoring group
overseeing the cease-fire in south Lebanon Tuesday started its
first session since Israel launched a massive air strike on
Lebanon in June.
</P>
<P>
The group is to hear a record 37 complaints, of which 16 filed
by Lebanon and 21 by Israel at Naqoura near Israeli border, where
the United Nations peacekeeping force is headquartered.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the protests stems from the violence last
month in which Israel warplanes killed 10 Lebanese and destroyed
the country's two power stations, a telephone relay station and
three bridges.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese President Emile Lahoud instructed the Lebanese
delegation to press for a condemnation of Israeli air raids.
</P>
<P>
But a Western diplomat source expected the meeting to be
concluded swiftly with an accusation on both Israel and Lebanese
guerrillas of violating the cease-fire agreement reached by two
sides.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-brokered deal, which ended the 16-day Israeli blitz
on Lebanon in April 1996, prohibits any attacks from or on
civilian targets in both countries.
</P>
<P>
The panel, consisting of representatives from the United
States, France, Syria, Lebanon and Israel, was established to
monitor the implementation of the agreement, but has no power to
act.
</P>
<P>
Former Israeli government of Benjamin Netanyahu, which launched
last month's raid, believed the panel useless for curbing violence
in south Lebanon and left the meeting to be handled by the new
government under Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has been fighting to
oust Israeli forces and its ally South Lebanon Army out of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
