<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
forthcoming state visit to Mongolia is a significant visit which
will inherit from the past legacy and open up a new future for the
development of relationship between China and Mongolia, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhang made the remarks at the regular press briefing in
response to a question.
</P>
<P>
The two countries forged diplomatic ties 50 years ago and
signed a treaty on friendly and cooperative relations five years
ago, According to the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
China and Mongolia, two friendly neighboring countries, boast
continuous development in political, economic and cultural fields
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
She particularly pointed out that the treaty on friendly and
cooperative relations signed in 1994 laid the legal foundation for
the growth of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, during the successful state visit to China paid by
Mongolia President Nachagyn Bagbandy last year, the two sides
agreed to build up a long-term, stable, healthy and mutually
trusted relationship based on good-neighborhood, friendship and
cooperation for the coming 21st century, she said. She described
such consensus as of "great significance to open up the future of
bilateral ties."
</P>
<P>
Jiang is to pay the visit from July 15 to 17 as guest of
Bagbandy. 
