<HEADLINE> HK Fashion Week Participators Increase 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 344 exhibitors from
14 countries and regions are showcasing their latest designs and
products in the Hong Kong Fashion Week for Spring/Summer 2000,
which opened Tuesday morning at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The number of participators this year increased by 10 percent
over last year. As Asia embarking on the road to economic recovery,
there are significant increases in the number of exhibitors from
south Korea, Thailand, Taiwan, China's mainland and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Other exhibitors are from Bangladesh, Germany, India, Indonesia,
Italy, Japan, Malaysia and the Philippines as well as the host,
Hong Kong, the world's second largest clothing exporter after
China's mainland.
</P>
<P>
One of the major highlights of the four-day event is the 22nd
Hong Kong Young Fashion Designers' Contest to be held Tuesday
night when 15 promising young Hong Kong designers present their
latest ideas and creations.
</P>
<P>
Rosanna Wong Yick-ming, a member of the Executive Council of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said that fashion,
like other business, relies heavily on open competition.
</P>
<P>
Challenge and competition provide a healthy atmosphere that
encourages innovation and creativity, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
A series of exciting catwalk extravaganzas will encompass the
Asian Fashion Designers' Show, the Hong Kong Designers' Fashion
parade, Hong Kong Fashion Flash Show Spring/Summer 2000, the Hong
Kong Fashion Designers Association Show, house shows of Walter Ma
and Barney Cheng presented by Zip magazines, and the Hong Kong
Collection Show.
</P>
<P>
These fashion presentations will feature collections from more
than 40 designers from Hong Kong and the region.
</P>
<P>
To enhance Hong Kong Fashion Week as an international fashion
forum which allows fashion professionals to exchange ideas on
future trends and market opportunities, there will be a seminar on
"the Manufacturing and Sales Trends of the China Garment Industry.
"
</P>
<P>
Fashion is constantly changing and those involved must keep
abreast with trends and be innovative in developing new ones along
the way if they want to succeed, Wong said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
