<DOCNO> XIE19990713.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, U.S. to Negotiate on Compensation of Embassy Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua)-- China and the United States are
going to negotiate over compensation on the casualties and damage
of properties caused by the U.S.-led NATO's attack of China's
embassy in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia on May 8th, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
She did not provide further details about the timing and place
of the forthcoming talks.
</P>
<P>
About a month ago, U.S. President's personal envoy and
Undersecretary of State Thomas Pickering came to Beijing and
presented to the Chinese government a U.S. government report on
the results of its investigation into the attack of the Chinese
embassy in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government declined the report as "unacceptable".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
