<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Shariful Islam, military attache of the Bangladesh Embassy
in Ankara, was wounded and his wife and son were killed by a
Bangladeshi servant on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Islam's servant Rahman Hafizar, 20, first went to the room of
Islam's 14-year-old son and stabbed him to death with a knife and
then killed Islam's wife.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit expressed his hope
that Britain would be of help to make the world realize that
there are two separate states on the island of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit said the fact that there are two separate states on the
island provides peace and stability there.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- United States Secretary of Defense William Cohen will arrive
in Turkey for a one-day visit as part of his six-country tour.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will visit the U.S. Incirlik Air Base in Adana, southern
Turkey, before arriving in Ankara. 
</P>
