<DOCNO> XIE19990713.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Step up Popularization of Quality Grain Seeds (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- China has worked out a series of
measures to accelerate the development and popularization of good
quality grain seeds to meet farmers' increasing demand following
the country's readjustment of its grain production mix, a Ministry
of Agriculture (MA) official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Due to good grain harvests for the past four consecutive years,
China has put an end to chronic grain shortages and has basically
balanced grain supply and demand.
</P>
<P>
Therefore the central government has decided to phase out price
protection for poor quality grain and oversupplied grain varieties
such as the spring wheat in northeast China, early long-grained
rice in south China, and winter wheat in areas south of Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
Farmers across China, regardless of profit or loss during the
summer harvest, have all come to realize that good quality grain
will bring them greater income in the long run.
</P>
<P>
"China in not in short supply of good quality grain seeds, but
the problem is that they are far from popular for a variety of
reasons," said Chen Youquan, deputy chief of the Seed and Plant
Quarantine Division under MA's Crop Production Department.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, priority will be given to cultivating and
popularizing good quality seeds, which have won state approval for
nationwide use, " he said.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has developed and approved 186 varieties of
high quality wheat, rice, maize, cotton and soybean seeds for
nationwide use, he said.
</P>
<P>
Of this total, more than 40 varieties of wheat and rice seeds
can be used in areas where the spring wheat of northeast China,
early long-grained rice of south China, and winter wheat south of
the Yangtze River are now grown.
</P>
<P>
China will also allow market forces to play a key role in
quickening the process of developing and popularizing quality
seeds, and encourage the establishment of enterprises that will
combine the functions of development, popularization, and sales of
these seeds, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
