<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, July 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen said here
Monday that it is imperative to improve the relations between
Russia and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Cohen told reporters after meeting Hungarian Foreign Minister
Martonyi Janos that Russia's participation in the Kosovo
international peacekeeping force (KFOR) is proceeding on schedule.
(Hungary-NATO-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia's finance ministry had uncovered 11,536
corruption cases involving 183.64 billion rupiah (28 million U.S.
dollars) from April 1997 to the end of last month, The Jakarta
Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Bambang Subianto said that more than 76
percent of the corruption was linked to tax fraud. (Indonesia-
Corruption)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States reaffirmed on Monday that its
position on Taiwan is unchanged and it will continue to follow the
"one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
James Foley, deputy spokesman for the State Department, made
the remarks at a news briefing in response to allegations by
Taiwan's Lee Teng-hui on July 9 that the cross-strait relations
should be "state-to-state" or at least "special state-to-state
relations". (US-China-Taiwan Issue)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Justice Department Monday charged
Japanese automaker Toyota with putting faulty smog-control
computers on 2.2 million 1996-1998 vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The department, on behalf of the Environmental Protection
Agency, filed a civil lawsuit against the Japanese company under
the Clean Air Act in U.S. District Court here, seeking to have the
computers repaired and the company fined up to 58.5 billion
dollars. (US-Japan-Toyota)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Refugees in Zambia will not return to Congo (K) until
the cease-fire agreement signed in Lusaka last Saturday is
implemented.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) said
until the cease-fire accord is fully implemented, it would
continue to look after the refugees who fled the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) when conflict broke out there early last
August. (Zambia-Congolese Refugees) 
</P>
</TEXT>
