<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Step up Popularization of Quality Grain Seeds (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As part of this process, China will introduce more good quality
grain seeds from overseas and encourage foreign seed research
institutions and companies to set up joint-ventures in the country,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 varieties of quality grain seeds have been
introduced since the government launched a program called the 948
Project, three years ago.
</P>
<P>
Of the 300 varieties, 77 performed well in regional trial
plantings, and the trial growing acreage now has expanded to more
than 400,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
But, Chen noted, China will not rely only on imported quality
seeds to meet domestic demand, and imported varieties will not be
allowed for nationwide use until they pass trial plantings and win
state approval.
</P>
<P>
"Some varieties of grain seeds abroad are indeed of good
quality, but they may not be adaptable to China's local
environment, so the import of quality seeds should be conducted in
a careful manner," said Liu Xu, head of the Institute of Crop
Germplasm Resources under the Chinese Academy of Agricultural
Science. 
</P>
</TEXT>
