<HEADLINE> Sino-American Cultural Exchange Summer Camp Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A four-week summer camp for Sino-
American cultural and language exchange opened Monday in this
capital of northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
Students from American universities will present a brief
introduction to their country's history, geography and culture to
Chinese students, who in turn will help their guests learn about
Chinese history, culture, religion and the life of ethnic groups
living in the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the students will host a series of exchange
activities including preparing Chinese dish, sports competitions,
and visits to Tibetan families and factories, schools, and
cultural centers.
</P>
<P>
Fred Wagner, the camp organizer from the United States, said
this summer camp aims to provide the students with a greater
understanding of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the camp will promote friendship between Chinese
and American students, he said.
</P>
<P>
This is the second such cultural exchange summer camp held in
Qinghai, cradle of the mother-rivers of Chinese civilization --
the Yangtze and the Yellow river.  
</P>
</TEXT>
