<HEADLINE> Papua New Guinea Elects New Parliament Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Papua New Guinea's parliament
Tuesday elected former deputy prime minister Iairo Lasaro as the
new speaker, reports from Port Moresby confirmed.
</P>
<P>
With the support of Advance PNG party, Iairo Lasaro was elected
by a majority of 57 to 45.
</P>
<P>
Leader of Advance PNG party John Pundari was nominated Tuesday
by the country's government as prime minister to replace Bill
Skate who resigned last week.
</P>
<P>
The parliament will vote on Wednesday on the nomination.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Pundari's Advance PNG party criticized Skate and left
the ruling coalition. Pundari then joined the ranks of the
opposition and became the opposition's candidate as deputy prime
minister. In return for the government's nomination as prime
minister, Pundari deserted the opposition coalition.
</P>
<P>
Pundari told reporters that after Skate's resignation, "we have
decided that we will continue this government." 
</P>
