<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Welcomes Indo-Pak Accord on Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has welcomed the
agreement between India and Pakistan for military disengagement in
the disputed Kashmir, The Bangladesh Observer newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome any step towards resolution of any conflict in the
region," acting Foreign Secretary Mohiuddin Ahmed said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Bangladesh always believes in the peaceful resolution of
disputes and conflicts," he said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing relief at this positive development between Dhaka's
two neighboring countries, Ahmed said, "We welcome this because
conflict leads to tension that adversely affects our
socio-economic development."
</P>
<P>
Press reports said India and Pakistan reached an agreement on
disengagement in Kashmir on Sunday, which was aimed at halting the
firing in the region between the two sides since May this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
