<HEADLINE> Jordan Urging Hill to Finish Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Jordan Formula One team chief Eddie
Jordan on Monday said he hoped Damon Hill's fifth-place finish at
Sunday's British Grand Prix was enough motivation to keep the
former world drivers' champion racing.
</P>
<P>
Jordan said: "After Damon's performance I am not so sure he
will want to stop", "It is up to him but the team is behind him
and would like him to continue if he can drive the way he drove (
at Silverstone)."
</P>
<P>
38-year-old Hill hinted at quitting immediately after crashing
out of the French GP last month and was still undecided about
racing at Silverstone until days before Sunday's race.
</P>
<P>
The British Grand Prix was expected to the last for the 1996
world champion but, with testing scheduled for Wednesday in Italy,
Hill still hasn't notified the team of his decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
