<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Hosts ASEAN Meeting on Transport, Communications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The seventh meeting of senior
transport and communication officials of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) is being held in Vietnam's Ho Chi
Minh City.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting, which opened on Monday by Vietnamese
Deputy Minister of Transport and Communications La Ngoc Khue, is a
preparation for the fifth ASEAN transport ministerial meeting
scheduled to be held in Hanoi on September 15 and 16, press
reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Discussions at the meeting are focusing on a program of action
for the ASEAN transport and communications sector in the 1999-2004
period, an ASEAN transport ministerial memorandum of understanding
on the development of an ASEAN road network, four protocols on the
implementation of the ASEAN framework agreement facilitating
on-transit goods, a draft ASEAN framework agreement facilitating
international communications and another on multi-modal
communications.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed measures to strengthen transport and
communications cooperation among ASEAN countries, particularly on
settlement of the year 2000 computer problem, transporting
travelers by sea, sea port cooperation, and urban traffic.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Vietnam hosts such a meeting. Eighty
senior officials from the transport sector of the 10 ASEAN member
countries and the ASEAN Secretariat are attend the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
