<HEADLINE> China Has 900 Listed Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong-based Kelon
Electrical Appliances Co., Ltd, went to public in Shenzhen Stock
Exchange today, bringing the total number of the country's listed
companies to 900.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Securities hailed the new listing, saying that
China's securities market has entered into a new stage of
development with 900 listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Along with new listings, the daily said, listed companies as a
whole have improved their performance and quality while the
necessary rules and regulations have been established for the
healthy development of the securities market.
</P>
<P>
Kelon Electrical Appliances, which is also listed in Hong Kong,
is a subsidiary of the Kelon Group, China's largest refrigerator
producer in the southern city of Shunde. It reported annual
business revenues totaling 5.57 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that up to July 9, altogether 980 shares of 899
companies were listed on the stock exchanges in Shanghai and
Shenzhen, including 873 A shares for domestic investors and 107 B
shares for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
In 1991 when the two bourses started operation, there were only
eight companies listed in Shanghai and another six in Shenzhen.
</P>
