<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed, 22
injured and 13 others missing in a landslide at Hunedoara in
western Romania, a television report said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The serious landslide followed heavy rains, which caused the
Riu Mare River in Retezatului Mountain to overflow its banks. The
floods inundated the area near a dam under construction and the
workers' residential area.
</P>
<P>
The prefect of Hunedoara county said local traffic was
suspended and rescue teams had to reach the disaster area by
military helicopters.
</P>
<P>
All the injured have been flown out to hospitals, and the local
victims will be quickly transferred to safe places, he added.
</P>
<P>
In the past 24 hours, heavy rain, hailstone and floods hit the
western and central parts of Romania, while an unprecedented hot
wave prevailed in the eastern and southern areas. Weather
forecasts said such climate will continue for several days.
</P>
