<HEADLINE> 66,000 Flood-Besieged Tourists Get Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, HUBEI, July 13 (Xinhua) -- About 66,000 Chinese and
foreign tourists besieged at the Three Gorges Dam area by recent
flooding have all been transferred to safe places.
</P>
<P>
Temporary locks at the Three Gorges Dam site on the Yangtze
River have been shut down twice for seven days since June 30
because of the rising water level caused by heavy rainfalls on the
upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
The Yichang city government has mobilized 1,700 motor vehicles
to transfer the 66,000 tourists, including 1,500 foreigners, from
358 ships.
</P>
<P>
According to Three Gorges Project Development Corporation
officials, ships can pass through the locks safely only when the
water flow is slower than 45,000 cubic meters per second.
</P>
<P>
The temporary locks have reportedly been reopened on Saturday
as the water level of the river has begun declining. 
</P>
