<HEADLINE> Chile Exports Less Wine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Wine exports from Chile during
the first five months this year fell 7.5 percent to 175.9 million
U.S. dollars in comparison with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Association of Fine Wines for Export show
that Japan imported 78 percent less of Chilean wine worth only 9.7
million dollars from the Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
The United States, the biggest Chilean wine importer, imported
41.688 million dollars of wine from Chile, down 0.3 percent
compared with the same period last year. 
</P>
