<HEADLINE> Duberry Joins Leeds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League football
club Chelsea defender Michael Duberry is to join Leeds United in a
transfer deal thought to be worth 4.5 million pounds.
</P>
<P>
The deal is subject to a medical but the defender is in Leeds
and it is hoped that he will sign later on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Leeds chairman Peter Ridsdale said: "Michael is having a
medical today and we have agreed personal terms."
</P>
<P>
"As soon as he passes the medical, we will sign him, so
hopefully that will be tonight."
</P>
<P>
While Duberry is set to join the west Yorkshire club, another
player is set to leave.
</P>
<P>
Striker Clyde Wijnhard has met with Huddersfield officials to
thrash out a possible one million punds move to the McAlpine
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Now Leeds are waiting to hear the outcome of those discussions.
</P>
<P>
"We're waiting to hear if Clyde has agreed personal terms. He
has met them but we haven't heard what has happened yet," Ridsdale
added.
</P>
<P>
But Leeds are refusing to comment on the possible signing of
Michael Bridges from Sunderland.
</P>
<P>
The forward pulled out of a deal to take him to Tottenham and
Ridsdale is wary of speaking out before negotiations have begun.
</P>
<P>
"We are making no comment about that at this stage," Ridsdale
said.
</P>
<P>
"Clearly, after what happened with Spurs last week, it is
inappropriate to make any comment. If and when there is any
comment,we will say it," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
