<HEADLINE> Graf to Retire at End of Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany's super star Steffi
Graf officially confirmed in New York on Monday she would retire
at the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
Graf, 30, said: "I must say this will be my last season.
</P>
<P>
"I am privileged to be able to leave when I wish without being
pushed towards the exit door. It was not easy to take this
decision but the competition had become too difficult for me."
</P>
<P>
Asked what would be her last tournament Graf said: "I haven't
really thought about that question yet."
</P>
<P>
When she quits Graf will help train young German prospects with
her enterprise, Sports Management Company. She said: "It's
something I am looking forward to with impatience." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
