<HEADLINE> Brazil to Keep Several Stars at Home in Confederation Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazil announced on Monday that
they would not send several top players to play the Confederations
Cup to be held later this month in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Strikers Ronaldo and Amoroso, full-backs Cafu and Roberto
Carlos and midfielder Rivaldo were all given time to rest and
prepare for the next European season.
</P>
<P>
Instead, coach Wanderley Luxemburgo opted to bring in younger
players including uncapped goalkeeper Renato, striker Warley,
defender Luis Alberto and left-back Athirson.
</P>
<P>
The squad was announced in the border town of Foz de Iguacu,
where Brazil have based themselves for the Copa America in
neighbouring Paraguay. 
</P>
