<HEADLINE> Sampras to Play Doubles in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras, now ranked third
in the world, will not be playing singles for the Unites States in
this weekend's Davis Cup quarter-finals against Australia in
Boston.
</P>
<P>
Sampras and his Davis Cup teammates were together for the first
time Monday in preparation for the matches at Longwood Cricket
Club.
</P>
<P>
Despite a hot streak and entreaties from teammate Todd Martin,
Sampras insisted that as a late arrival on a team that has earned
a quarter-final berth without him, his place is in doubles with
partner Alex O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
Only injuries to Jim Courier or Martin, the current singles duo,
could make him reconsider, Sampras said. 
</P>
