<HEADLINE> United States Claims Men's Basketball Title in Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Top favorite the United
States scored for a comfortable victory of 79-65 against
Yugoslavia, taking the men's basketball title at the 20th
Universiade here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Americans established their lead 42-31 at half break,
before running towards the top podium by outscoring their
Yugoslavian peers 37-34 in the second half.
</P>
<P>
However, the 2.03-meter M. Sekularac of Yugoslavia became the
top scorer with 31 points, almost half of the points of his team,
with teammate N. Pistoljejic added 11, while other 10 cagers
contributed a miserable 21 points in total, including two
scoreless players.
</P>
<P>
Martin Kenyon was the top scorer for the United States with 21
points, added by Mickeal Pete with 12, and M. Santangelo
contributed nine.
</P>
<P>
Although they scored eight three-pointers in 19 attempts
against four out of 13 attempts for the United States, the
Yugoslavians were beaten in both rebounds with 23 against 31 and
in free throws wherein the Americans made 11 out of 12 attempts.
</P>
<P>
In the third-place match, the hosts Spain outscored Mexico 90-
78 as the Spaniards outpowered the visitors 48-38 in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
The 1.90-meter F. Vazquez scored 20 points for the hosts, added
by Lluis Martinez with 17 and Juan Bernabe with 14. Both Martin
Ferrer and B. Alvarez contributed nine points apiece.
</P>
<P>
Zuniga Enrique scored 20 points for Mexico, added by Najera
Eduardo with 19 points.
</P>
<P>
Canada beat Russia 88-72 to finish fifth while Lithuania
outscored Brazil for the seventh place.
</P>
<P>
From ninth to 23rd places were Greece, Turkey, the Netherlands,
Britain, the Czech Republic, Finland, Belgium, Japan, South Korea,
Peru, South Africa and Ireland.
</P>
<P>
China finished in a distant 21st place, followed by Nigeria and
Hong Kong, China, while Germany was absent from the tournament.
</P>
