<HEADLINE> Spain Beats U.S. to Take Women's Basketball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 12 (Xinhua) -- In a heated low-scoring final,
the hosts Spain defeated the United States 57-48 to take the women
's basketball title here Monday evening at the 20th University
Games.
</P>
<P>
Rallied from the cheering audience, the Spanish women cagers
proved to be hard nuts for the pre-tournament favorites and become
the only team remained unbeaten till their eventual victory.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniards established a 32-26 lead at half break and
outscored their peers 25-22 in the second half, with 1.76-meter
Sanchez Rosaura scoring the most of 14 points.
</P>
<P>
Llamas Nieves, at a height of 1.91 meters, was the only other
Spaniard who scored in double digit with 13, while the Americans
also had two players in double digit as 1.83-meter Douglas Kathryn
scored 14 and 1.93-meter Riley Ruth 11.
</P>
<P>
Both sides had a poor showing in the three-points as the
Spaniard scored one out of their 18 attempts, while the Americans
triumphed once in 12 attempts.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard resorted to tight defense to force the Americans
for a 27 percent in field goals, while the hosts recorded their
higher 41 percent, which reduced the deficit of 12 free throws
against 13 and 39 rebounds against 44.
</P>
<P>
In the third place match, Russia outscored its Ukrainian peers
77-71 this afternoon, with the fifth place taken by Lithuania who
defeated Chinese Taipei on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ranked from seventh to 16th places are Canada, Portugal, China,
Sweden, the Czech Republic, Japan, Brazil, Mexico, South Korea and
South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
