<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Tributary Embankment Collapse Under Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A 210-meter embankment on a small
tributary of Yangtze River, which collapsed in recent flooding,
has been repaired.
</P>
<P>
The Dongjing River joins the main stream of the Yangtze near
the city of Wuhan and the city of Xiantao in Hubei Province. On
June 28, a cave-in was reported on embankments near where the
Dongjing meets the Yangtze and cracks were found on the inner
sides of other embankments.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters
organized people to repair the dangerous cave-in and, after more
than a week, the emergency repair work was completed with 20,000
cu.m. of earth and stone and new platforms being built inside the
embankments, according to Pan Rongzhou, chief engineer of the
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The second flood crest on the Yangtze was expected to pass
Wuhan Monday.
</P>
<P>
Flooding caused by heavy rainfall along the Yangtze River
Valley since late June has killed more than 200 people and
threatened the lives of 60 million local people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
