<HEADLINE> Seven People Killed in Shooting in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were found shot to
death Monday in Atlanta, capital of Georgia State of the United
States, with the only survivor an 11-year-old boy who hid a closet
for hours after he was wounded, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Five adults and two children were found shot to death in a
house in Atlanta City. The motive for the shootings was unclear,
but police were investigating whether one person killed the others
and himself.
</P>
<P>
"The possibility does exist that one of the persons inside, who
is also deceased, is responsible for all the shootings and that
injury to himself was self-inflicted," Deputy Police Chief C.B.
Jackson said.
</P>
<P>
Police stayed outside the house for more than an hour because a
dog was barking inside, raising safety concerns. Inside, officers
found at least one weapon and bodies throughout the house. The boy
told police the shooting started around 6 a.m. (local time).
</P>
</TEXT>
