<HEADLINE> Greek, Iranian, Armenian Officials Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 12 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Foreign Ministers of Greece,
Iran and Armenia held talks here Monday within the framework of
tripartite cooperation between the three countries.
</P>
<P>
Greece's Alternate Foreign Minister Yiannos Kranidiotis
stressed the political significance of such tripartite cooperation
in efforts to stabilize peace in the wider region and referred to
a need to strengthen economic cooperation between the three
countries, particularly in the energy sector, a Greek Foreign
Ministry announcement said.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed that the coordinating committee's next meeting
will take place in Yerevan, where the third meeting, at the
Foreign Ministers' level, will be held on September 7-8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
