<HEADLINE> Dow Sets New Record On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
climbed to the record high while most other indexes fell Monday
before the impending floods of second quarter corporate earning
reports.
</P>
<P>
The dow closed up 7.28 at 11,200.98, topping the record
closing high of 11,193.70, set last Friday. The index rose
2,019.55 points or 22 percent so far this year.
</P>
<P>
General Motors led the Dow higher. American Express,
International Paper, Chevron and Eastman Kodak also helped the
index to the new record.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 4.18 at 1,399.10 and the technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index fell 2.63 at 2,790.44.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 1.89 at 655.79. But the
American Stock Exchange index rose 2.81 at 815.54 and th Russell
2000 index of smaller companies rose 1.32 at 459.30.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-6 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,624 down, 1,381 up and 559
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 668.87 million shares from 556.50
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
